Login Using Brower
--------------------
if you are new:
 - atlas setup
 - atlas auth login

OR use Public/Private API Keys:
 $ atlas auth login --publicKey "<YOUR_PUBLIC_KEY>" --privateKey "<YOUR_PRIVATE_KEY>"
ðŸ”‘ API keys can be created from the MongoDB Atlas dashboard under:
Organization â†’ Access Manager â†’ API Keys



Create a Cluster
-----------------
 $ atlas clusters create myCluster \
  --provider AWS \
  --region US_EAST_1 \
  --tier M0 \
  --mongodb-version 7.0
  
ðŸ“Œ M0 is a free tier cluster. You can change the name, provider, and region as needed.

Whitelist your IP Address
----------------------------
Allow all IPs (development only)
$ atlas accessList create --ip 0.0.0.0
Allow a specific IP
$ atlas accessList create --ip <your-ip-address>



Create a Database User
-----------------------
atlas dbusers create \
  --username myUser \
  --password myPassword123 \
  --role readWriteAnyDatabase \
  --authDatabase admin

Get Connection String
-------------------------
atlas clusters connectionStrings describe --clusterName myCluster

you'll get a connection string like:
mongodb+srv://myUser:<password>@myCluster.abcd123.mongodb.net/?retryWrites=true&w=majority


full setup onliner
--------------------
atlas auth login
atlas clusters create myCluster --provider AWS --region US_EAST_1 --tier M0
atlas accessList create --ip 0.0.0.0
atlas dbusers create --username myUser --password myPassword123 --role readWriteAnyDatabase --authDatabase admin
atlas clusters connectionStrings describe --clusterName myCluster











